# SANKO VISION DEMO — PHASE 5: Regulator View

## Context
Phases 1-4 built the project, data, Home, Practitioner, and Researcher views. Now build the Regulator view.

## What to build
Create src/views/RegulatorView.jsx and import it into App.jsx.

## Layout
Max-width 1100px, centered, padding 24px.

## State
```jsx
const [selectedCity, setSelectedCity] = useState(null);
const [expandedSignal, setExpandedSignal] = useState(null);
const [expandedFormulation, setExpandedFormulation] = useState(null);
const [hoveredBar, setHoveredBar] = useState(null);
```

## Components

### Header
- Gold badge: "🏛️ Sanko Governance Dashboard"
- Title (serif, 24px): "Traditional medicine — population-level intelligence"
- Subtitle: "Real-time data on traditional medicine usage, outcomes, and safety signals across Nigeria."

### Top-level stats (5 column grid)
- 12,400 active practitioners (green)
- 54,200 formulations documented
- 186,000 patient outcomes tracked
- 82% national avg effectiveness (green)
- 3 active safety signals (terra/red)

### Two-column layout below stats

**Left column: Interactive map**
Card titled "Usage density by state"

Create an abstract dot map using CITIES from data.js. Position dots using the x,y percentages from the data as left/top percentages on a 100% × 200px container with a dark green-tinted background.

Each dot:
- 10px circle, forest green with box-shadow glow
- Pulse animation (subtle)
- City name label above (9px, muted)
- **Clickable**: onClick → setSelectedCity(city)
- If this city is selectedCity, show it larger (14px) and brighter

**When a city is selected**, show a detail panel below the map (or as a slide-out):
- City name (bold, 16px)
- Stats: "{practitioners} practitioners · {formulations} formulations"
- Top conditions as tag pills
- "Close ×" button

**Right column: Conditions bar chart**
Card titled "Top conditions treated"

Vertical bar chart using CSS (flexbox with items aligned to bottom):
```
Malaria/Fever: 32% (59,520 cases)
Diabetes: 18% (33,480)
Cough/Respiratory: 14% (26,040)
Hypertension: 11% (20,460)
Digestive: 8% (14,880)
Pain: 6% (11,160)
Other: 11% (20,460)
```

Each bar:
- Height proportional to percentage (32% = full height)
- Forest green, decreasing opacity for lower bars
- Label below (9px)
- Percentage above (10px)
- **Hover**: show a tooltip with exact case count: e.g. "Malaria/Fever: 32% · 59,520 tracked cases"

### Pharmacovigilance signals
Card with header: "⚠️ Active pharmacovigilance signals" (terra coloured) + subtitle "Auto-detected from outcome data"

Use SAFETY_SIGNALS from data.js. Show each as a row/card:
- Title (bold)
- Region | Reports count | Severity badge (Moderate=gold, Mild=grey) | Status badge (Under review=blue, Investigating=blue, Monitoring=grey)

**Clickable** → toggles expandedSignal:
When expanded, show:
- Full detail text
- "Ingredients involved:" + ingredient names as tags
- "Timeline:" + timeline text
- "Recommended action:" + action text
- Border changes to terra colour when expanded

Small note at bottom: "Signals generated when 3+ independent practitioners report similar adverse events for formulations sharing common ingredients. No individual practitioner or patient identified."

### Formulations of regulatory interest
Card with header + subtitle "Crossed statistical thresholds for evidence-based registration"

Table with columns: ID | Condition | Outcomes | Effectiveness | Side effects | Readiness

Show FORMULATIONS where effectiveness >= 80 (should be f1, f2, f4, f5). Use anonId for the ID column.

**Clickable rows** → toggles expandedFormulation:
When expanded, show:
- Full ingredient list (botanical names)
- Outcome breakdown bar
- "Geographic distribution: primarily Southwest Nigeria" (for all in this demo)
- Note: "This formulation meets the evidence threshold for expanded registration review under the proposed traditional medicine regulatory pathway."

### Flywheel footer
Same subtle bar at bottom.

